						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar stone supporting Nandi, Ādhipurīśvara temple (west face).</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">M.K. Parakēsarivarman (Parāntaka I) Year 40: 947 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records that Nakkaṉ Parāntakaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Brahmaśrīrājaṉ (a resident) of Alaiyūr a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Mipilāṟu in Poygai-nāḍu on the northern bank (of the river Kāvēri) in Chōḷa-nāḍu made a gift of ninety sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to the god of Tiruvoṟṟiyūr.</p>						

						</summary>
